Ladakh Trip Day - 1

Shanti Stupa -> Leh Palace -> Leh Market

Since it was the first day and were didn’t sleep for almost 36hrs coz of travel and same time didn’t water to waste the day resting in hotel. We chose to Visit nearby places 

Since it’s November it’s quite cold but same time Pros of visiting this place are

👉 Less Tourist therefore you can easily go around 
👉 You will be able to see snowy beauty of the city 
👉 Hotel prices are less compare to peak season
👉 Since it’s the beginning of November all the spots are open and accessible 

Cons
👉 It’s chilling cold therefore you will have to carry more winter wear
👉 Limited local Restaurants are open 

Very soon I will make a blog on how to style and look your best even during peak winter

Day - 3 Travelling to #Ladakh in November
—> #pangonglake 

👉It’s a must visit Place when you come to Ladakh. 

👉From Leh it’s 240kms and approximately 4 to 5 hrs depending on the roads

👉Three most important things to take care of when you travelling to Pangong Lake during winter 🥶 

——-> Wear proper thermals and woollen wear

——-> Carry postpaid Ajio/BSNL number. Other network/Prepaid network doesn’t work over there.

——-> Carry Motion sickness medicine and ORS. Also Portable Oxygen Cylinder, which is available in hotel mostly.

Being an stylist I planned my outfit well in advance where I combined camouflage pants with white sweater and white woollen Beanie - all from @myntra

How to combine Black and White Outfits 😀

99% of our closest will have Black and White Outfits
👉 As you can combine this with any colour 
👉 Also a full proof way to look professional 

But black and white can be boring and wear wrongly you may look bigger 

So for wearing black and white here are few rules to abide by👇👇👇

1. Never wear 50% of black - 50% white

2. Try wearing in uneven percentage as 60%-40% | 70%-30% | 80%-20%

@mrsindiaworldwide_official was that motivation for me and now in 2019 June I am weighing again 54kgs... It’s about healthy eating and 20mins if exercise everyday. Also, giving importance to those small activities that we miss on daily basis like: 
1. Taking stairs
2. Walking for 5min after every one hour
3. Drinking lots of water
4. Eating dinner early

Do you guys take care of your hair?
.
To make your hair look bouncy here are few tips 😀
.
❤️ Use hair mask before wash 
❤️ Wash your hair twice a week - not everyday 
❤️Always use serum after was incase you don’t have serum two drops if oil 
❤️ like colouring your hair - always check your skin tone fir the right Color 
❤️ Leave an inch from your roots while colouring so that it doesn’t damages your root
.

It’s very important to select right hair colour based on your skin tone... mine is ‘ash gold’ as I have warm - autumn skin tone
.
Mostly all Indians have warm skin tone but under the "warm" skin tone category, there are two different types (autumn and summer).

Depending on which type you are, there will be specific hair colors that suit you best
.
Summer skin tone - Golden Blonde, Caramel Brown, Champagne Blonde, Honey or Butter Platinum
.

Autumn skin tone - Rich Auburn, Chocolate Brown, Honey Blonde, Ash gold
.

Day - 4 Travelling to #Ladakh in November 

#Leh -> #khardunglapass -> #nubravalley 

Without Snow ❄️ I really feel view would have been incomplete… 

👉Myth
-It’s a myth that you cannot go to Ladakh in November. Early November is the best time when you can see the snow and all the tourists places are open from Pangong Lake, Khardungla pass, Nubra valley etc

👉Facts 
-Ladakh is open for tourist all around the year and within Ladakh everything remains open

- You can visit Ladakh even during winter by flight to Leh

-After November Winter takes a peak and if you love to experience that, you can visit Ladakh

-In mid winters there are times because of snow roads are blocked but Indian military clears them asap

- Yes, if you are planning for the road trip then the highways are closed. Ex Manali highway or Srinagar highway 

👉Tips TO TRAVEL IN NOVEMBER👈

-To experience the snow start early morning by 6 or 6:30 am from Leh. During the day time you will not find so much snow ❄️ around 

Had an amazing unforgettable experience in these 4 days. November is when in the snow starts, it’s cold and you can see more beautiful Ladakh

- Carry good quality thermals, woollens and winter shoes

-Carry doctor prescribed medicines for high altitude breathing issue (anytime of the year regardless of winters) and motion sickness tablets 

-Ask for the portable oxygen cylinder in hotel or to your taxi driver (regardless of the season)

- First day visit places within the city to get used to of the temperature and high altitude area

-Don’t worry if you have missed carrying some winter wear there are many reasonable winter wear shops.

Fine Dining Etiquette 🥗🥂🍽
.

Dining skills say a lot about a person🍷
.

And not knowing it can be more damaging than you would think, especially for people in high positions
.

Table manners are about more than using the correct cutlery and napkin protocol🍽🥂🥢
.
When you are at a business dinner or formal gathering, you aren't there to fill your stomach😋. It's an opportunity to network, exchange knowledge and you want to focus on that
.
Here are some quick fine dining etiquette that will help to get corporate success 😊 🍷Never Lift your menu off the table
. 🍷Once you sip from the glass you must sip from exact same place on that glass for the rest of the evening .
🍷Don’t clink not even for the ‘gram, in very formal dining less noise we make, the better
.
🍷Keep the time of your plates as clean as possible,  this is out of respect for the service staff who clear the plate
.
🍷Place discards on upper left of your plate
.
🍷Keep your breast on the plate at all the times unless you deliver it to your mouth
.
🍷Fold the napkin with the crease toward you before putting it in your lap
.
🍷Leave one bite on your plate, this shows that you enjoyed the meal, but you weren’t so famished you cleaned the whole plate
.
🍷Never day you are going to the restroom, if you have to then excuse yourself but do not say why!
.
🍷Don’t day “Bon appetite”, it’s sounds just like an invitation for a good digestion and suggest that you are so hungry that you may jump on any food that would cross your mouth .

Day - 3 Travelling to #Ladakh in November
—> #pangonglake 

👉It’s a must visit Place when you come to Ladakh. 

👉From Leh it’s 240kms and approximately 4 to 5 hrs depending on the roads

👉Three most important things to take care of when you travelling to Pangong Lake during winter 🥶 

——-> Wear proper thermals and woollen wear

——-> Carry postpaid Ajio/BSNL number. Other network/Prepaid network doesn’t work over there.

——-> Carry Motion sickness medicine and ORS. Also Portable Oxygen Cylinder, which is available in hotel mostly.

Being an stylist I planned my outfit well in advance where I combined camouflage pants with white sweater and white woollen Beanie - all from @myntra

Travel 🧳 during pandemic is risky but certain times we cannot avoid travelling
.
Specially when it comes to corporate or a day business travel
.
Here are the list of the item you need to carry for your one day Business travel
.
1. Extra set of clothes - in case of emergency or you might want to change in the later part of the day
.
2. Perfume, body mist & mouth fresher - very important to smell good and maintain hygiene 
.
3. Tissue, wet wipes, mask & Sanitizer - needless to say how important these stuff are 
.
4. Pair of flats & sunglasses 🕶- to make yourself comfortable during the day
.
5. Makeup pouch- basic makeup pouch to make you presentable at any point in day
.
